  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (NC-9 clean)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Evidence carries explicitly low confidence scores and wide uncertainty bounds, each documented honestly with full rationale. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed across all five flow-speed operating points. Despite elevated uncertainty, all 13 credibility factors are assessed; achieved levels meet or exceed required levels at MRL 5. The decision is Accepted with documented residual risk: the team acknowledges that wide hemolysis prediction intervals (±38% at 95% CI) constitute residual epistemic uncertainty that must be monitored in post-market surveillance. No weakener fires; this is a structurally clean package.",
